      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] fix gateway hot-mode restart reloads",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCloses the silent-staleness hole in `gateway.reload.mode: \"hot\"` without changing the shipped default contract. Hot mode keeps warn-and-keep for routine restart-required config edits; two scoped behaviors layer on top:\n\n- **`gateway.reload.autoRestartOnRequired: true`** (new optional key, default `false`): opt-in that delegates restart-required edits to the gateway's existing idle-aware restart path, matching `mode: \"hybrid\"` for the restart-required branch while keeping hot-safe edits hot.\n- **Security-critical carve-out** (always on): restart reasons under `gateway.auth.*` and `secrets.*` schedule a restart even in default hot mode. Without this, a `gateway.auth.token` rotation or `secrets.providers.*` change on disk sits behind warn-and-keep while the runtime keeps honoring the compromised credential.\n\nAn earlier draft of this PR made hot mode schedule restarts unconditionally; review correctly flagged that as a semantic change to the shipped `hot` contract, and the current shape supersedes it. Existing `mode: \"hot\"` deployments are behavior-stable on upgrade for routine edits.\n\n## Details\n\n- `src/gateway/config-reload.ts`: restart-required plans in hot mode now branch three ways — warn-and-keep (default), `hot mode scheduling restart per gateway.reload.autoRestartOnRequired=true` (opt-in), and `hot mode scheduling restart for security-critical change (...)` (always). The existing idle-aware restart machinery (`queueRestart`) remains the only restart path; this PR adds no new restart mechanism.\n- `SECURITY_CRITICAL_RESTART_PREFIXES = [\"gateway.auth\", \"secrets\"]` — the `secrets` prefix is top-level, fixing the review-found P1 where an earlier `gateway.secrets` prefix could never match real restart reasons; `src/gateway/config-reload-plan.ts` now marks `secrets.providers.*` restart-required so the carve-out has a live trigger.\n- `gateway.reload.autoRestartOnRequired` added to `src/config/types.gateway.ts`, `zod-schema.ts` (strict validation), `schema.help.ts`, `schema.labels.ts`.\n- Regression tests in `src/gateway/config-reload.test.ts` pin each branch: warn-and-keep preserved on non-security edits; opt-in queues a supervised restart; security-critical auth/secrets changes restart regardless of the opt-in; plus the doctor-style model-route repair still hot-reloads when no restart-only path is present.\n- Docs updated: `docs/gateway/configuration-reference.md`, `docs/gateway/configuration.md`, `docs/gateway/index.md` describe the default, the opt-in, and the carve-out.\n\n**Open maintainer decision:** this adds one config key on a compatibility-sensitive surface. The default split (warn-and-keep stays default; auth/secrets always restart) is the proposed contract — if a different split is preferred (e.g. opt-in defaulting `true` for fresh installs only), say the word and I will adjust.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: in hot reload mode, a config write touching any restart-required key was dropped with a single `log.warn` while the gateway kept serving from the stale in-memory snapshot. Observed in production as a 4-hour silent outage where the agent kept resolving the legacy `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` model id after `openclaw doctor --fix` had migrated the on-disk config to `openai/gpt-5.5`; group messages silently dropped, admin DMs returned a canned `[agent failed]` reply. With this patch, security-critical edits (auth/secrets) self-heal via restart by default, and operators can opt all restart-required edits into the same path.\n\n- **Real environment tested**: isolated sandbox gateway on macOS (loopback port 28789), dist built from this branch; plus the original production incident capture on a launchd-supervised deployed gateway (`gateway-host`) documenting the pre-fix failure mode. Sandbox scenarios were captured at commit `d023afb9c4` (the commit introducing the opt-in + carve-out design); the secrets-prefix P1 fix and rebase landed after and are pinned by regression tests.\n\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: for each scenario, start a fresh sandbox gateway from the branch dist, wait for the config watcher to settle, write one config edit, observe the reload log and process state.\n  ```\n  Scenario A: mode \"hot\" (defaults), edit gateway.bind \"loopback\" -> \"lan\"\n  Scenario B: mode \"hot\" + autoRestartOnRequired true, same edit\n  Scenario C: mode \"hot\" (defaults), rotate gateway.auth.token\n  ```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  ```\n  A: [reload] config reload requires gateway restart; hot mode ignoring (gateway.bind)\n     process state: RUNNING (pid=8610, uptime 00:14)        # warn-and-keep preserved\n  B: [reload] config reload requires gateway restart; hot mode scheduling restart per gateway.reload.autoRestartOnRequired=true (gateway.bind)\n     [gateway] received SIGUSR1; restarting\n     [shutdown] started: gateway restarting\n     process state: RUNNING (pid=6706, uptime 00:15)        # restarted clean\n  C: [reload] config reload requires gateway restart; hot mode scheduling restart for security-critical change (gateway.auth.token)\n     [gateway] received SIGUSR1; restarting\n     process state: RUNNING (pid=9261, uptime 00:14)        # credential rotation propagated\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: scenario A proves existing hot-mode deployments keep the shipped warn-and-keep contract with no restart. Scenario B proves the opt-in routes routine restart-required edits through the existing SIGUSR1 + clean-shutdown restart path. Scenario C proves auth rotations propagate by default, closing the credential-rotation-bypass gap. The production failure mode (`hot mode ignoring` on `auth.profiles.*` for 4 hours) is eliminated for security-critical keys and operator-electable for everything else.\n\n- **What was not tested**: launchd auto-respawn end-to-end on hosts using `KeepAlive: { SuccessfulExit: false }` (see operator note below — the clean-exit hand-off needs a kickstart watcher on such hosts; not a regression, the pre-fix path also required manual intervention). The sandbox ran unmanaged (in-process restart mode); the managed-install launchd restart path is covered by existing integration tests. Scenario captures predate the final rebase; the post-rebase head is pinned by 360 passing gateway-config tests including the three branch-behavior regressions.\n\n## Operator note: launchd `SuccessfulExit=false` hosts\n\nHosts that set `KeepAlive: { Crashed=true, SuccessfulExit=false }` (to dodge an unrelated respawn cascade) will not auto-respawn after the restart hand-off's clean exit. The deployment fork pairs this with a 30s interval watchdog (`launchctl print` state AND port-binding check, then `launchctl kickstart -k`) — documented here so the gap flagged in review is paired with its operational answer. Hosts on default launchd `KeepAlive` semantics respawn normally and need nothing.\n",
        "branch": "codex/gateway-restart-required-diagnostics",
